unittitle_ssm: Records of the Gallatin Papers Project
abstract_ssm: The Gallatin Papers Project Began in 1958 and ended in 1970 with the publication of the microfilm edition of the Papers of Albert Gallatin.  The project was initiated in 1958 and run by Bayrd Still, the chairman of the History Department, who assigned various members of the History Department to manage the project.  The History Department sent the papers to the New York University Archives in 1978.
